[2026-03-18T17:14:00.119Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XQn4jUeZprD1P5JLj5UqL2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Problem:** `startRetentionJob` used `setInterval(86400000ms)` which drifts due to event-loop delays and container pauses. Frequent restarts meant the 24h interval never fired while the 5s startup timeout always did.\n\n**Fix — two files changed:**\n\n1. **`packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts`** — Added `system_kv` table to the system DB schema for persisting key-value state across restarts.\n\n2. **`packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`** — Replaced the drifting `setInterval(24h)` with:\n   - A **60-second wall-clock poll** that checks `utcToday()` against the DB-persisted `retention_last_run_date`\n   - Runs retention **exactly once per UTC calendar day** regardless of restarts or event-loop delays\n   - Persists the successful run date to `system_kv` after completion, so restarts don't re-run\n   - A `running` guard prevents overlapping executions if a run takes longer than 60s\n   - Failed runs are **not** recorded, so they retry on the next tick"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":398,"cache_read_input_tokens":56035,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":398},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bcae0c8d-0b02-4ad9-b283-350ffa4e6b87","uuid":"91418359-e7ee-4ce5-83f2-cc816d2b2af3"}
